properties.areaDesc: Ferris/Seminoe/Shirley Mountains; North Laramie Range; Converse County Lower Elevations; Shirley Basin
properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 4 at 2:35AM MST until February 4 at 5:00PM MST by NWS Cheyenne WY
properties.description:
...PERIODS OF SNOW WILL CONTINUE TO RESULT IN HAZARDOUS TRAVEL
CONDITIONS THIS MORNING...

* WHAT...Periods of snow. Additional accumulations less than one
inch expected.

* WHERE...Northern Carbon County and much of Converse County.

* WHEN...Until 5 PM MST this afternoon.

* IMPACTS...Travel will be hazardous due to icy and snow packed
roads and periods of low visibility.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 5 PM MST THIS AFTERNOON... ...WINTER STORM WARNING IS CANCELLED
